FBIS3-51636 "drlat015_b_94010" FBIS-LAT-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 Bermuda Haiti 19 Jan Chamber of Deputies Opening Aborted FL2001184594 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 GMT 20 Jan 93 FL2001184594 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] The opening of the Assembly session was aborted when only 30 deputies answered the second roll call. Chamber of Deputies President Frantz Robert Monde says that all measures that can be considered will be taken jointly with the majority in order to deal with this attempted boycott. Monde says it is shameful that parliamentarians who regularly receive their salaries are refusing to attend the sessions.
